save the children state of the world's m.data-term: save the children state of the world's mothers report

examples.en: Her face was alight with maternal pride.
Doctors are concerned about the effects of the drug on maternal health.
Seeing the baby aroused all her maternal instincts.
Her maternal instincts told her that something was wrong.
She seems to have a strong maternal instinct (=desire to have babies and take care of them).
The image of a mother suckling her babe is a standard artistic symbol of maternal love and nurturing.
Annie was wonderfully warm and maternal.
